There are only a few steps you need to take to clone this repository and start making contributions to our documentation.

1. Clone the repository

	git clone git@github.com:cohesivecc/admin-docs.git admin-docs
	cd admin-docs
	
2. Install the bundle

	bundle install
	
3. Install npm and bower if you don't have them already.

	Installing node and npm:
	https://docs.npmjs.com/getting-started/installing-node

	Install bower:
	npm install -g bower
	
4. Install the bower package.

	bower install
	
5. Link the project in puma-dev

	puma-dev link

6. This documentation web app should now be accessible via http://admin-docs.dev